@@ -519,6 +519,31 @@ A configuration file can be used to set the default
 - The options specified on the module command line override the values from the
   configuration file.
 
+[[logging]]
+== Logging
+
+pam_u2f always logs to syslog, via the `LOG_AUTHPRIV` facility, regardless
+of the `debug`/`loglevel` settings:
+
+- A successful FIDO authentication logs the public key of the credential
+  used and its index in the authorization mapping file, at `info` level.
+
+- A failed FIDO authentication logs the public key of the credential that
+  came closest to succeeding (if any) and the reason for the failure, at
+  `notice` level.
+
+- A configuration file that is rejected (wrong owner, unsafe permissions,
+  not a regular file, or unreadable) logs the reason, at `warning` level.
+
+Set `loglevel=warning` (or higher) to suppress the per-authentication audit
+records above while still receiving configuration warnings and errors. The
+public key logged on each attempt is not secret, but is identifying
+information; restrict access to the AUTHPRIV logs (typically
+`/var/log/auth.log` or `/var/log/secure`) accordingly.
+
+`debug` (or `loglevel=debug`) additionally enables verbose diagnostic
+messages at `debug` level, useful for troubleshooting.
+
