 Set the relying party ID for the FIDO authentication procedure. If no
@@ -190,6 +189,30 @@ A configuration file can be used to set the default module arguments.
 - The options specified on the module command line override the values from the
   configuration file.
 
+== LOGGING
+
+pam_u2f always logs to syslog(3), via the LOG_AUTHPRIV facility,
+regardless of the *debug*/*loglevel* settings:
+
+- A successful FIDO authentication logs the public key of the credential
+  used and its index in the authorization mapping file, at "info" level.
+
+- A failed FIDO authentication logs the public key of the credential that
+  came closest to succeeding (if any) and the reason for the failure, at
+  "notice" level.
+
+- A configuration file that is rejected (wrong owner, unsafe permissions,
+  not a regular file, or unreadable) logs the reason, at "warning" level.
+
+Set *loglevel*=_warning_ (or higher) to suppress the per-authentication
+audit records above while still receiving configuration warnings and
+errors. The public key logged on each attempt is not secret, but is
+identifying information; restrict access to the AUTHPRIV logs (typically
+/var/log/auth.log or /var/log/secure) accordingly.
+
+*debug* (or *loglevel*=_debug_) additionally enables verbose diagnostic
+messages at "debug" level, useful for troubleshooting.
+
 == NOTES
 
 *Nodetect*
